Corporate Social Responsibility: Not Just a Catch-all Company Strategy By Center for Social Policy Development of the Women’s Society of Friendship of the Council of Women in Business of Azerbayjan

Women’s NGO’s and all those charity organisations that work towards the promotion of women’s rights are key players in the process of the promotion of the status of women.

Improving the status of women is a multi-stakeholder effort and one of the major means for achieving this goal is partnership with International, National and Local Business enterprises. There is a large body of research on “Corporate Social Responsibility” and it is vital for women’s NGOs to take into consideration much of this research in order to help in raising awareness of the importance of adopting a principle of CSR amongst Azerbaijani Enterprises. Yet more research is needed in Azerbaijan, since Cororate Social Responsibility is mainly the domain of the western NGO’s.

The eradication of poverty, sustainability, human rights and active commitment to corporate responsibility and mutual cooperation is the basic principle of Corporate Social Responsibility.
